  ---

⏺ UX DESIGN RECOMMENDATIONS FOR EPC CONTEXT

  ★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────
  Design Thinking for EPC: The electrical & solar panel EPC industry has unique characteristics:
  1. Project-centric operations - Everything revolves around projects (sales, costs, materials, labor)
  2. Field + Office workflow - Workers on-site need mobile-friendly, simplified interfaces
  3. Cash flow sensitivity - Down payments, progress billing, retention are critical
  4. Material planning complexity - Long lead times for panels/inverters require forward planning
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────

  1. VALUE PROPOSITION PER USER

  | User        | Primary Value                             | Key Metric to Show                          |
  |-------------|-------------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------|
  | Owner       | "Is my business healthy?"                 | Cash position, project margins, overdue AR  |
  | Sales       | "How many deals can I close?"             | Pipeline value, win rate, quote aging       |
  | PM          | "Will I finish on time & budget?"         | Project progress, cost vs budget, WO status |
  | Procurement | "Do I have what I need?"                  | Shortages, PO status, supplier performance  |
  | Warehouse   | "Where is it & how much?"                 | Stock levels, pending requisitions          |
  | Finance     | "Is money coming in/going out correctly?" | AR aging, AP schedule, cash flow            |

  2. DESIGN PRINCIPLES

  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │                           UX DESIGN PRINCIPLES                                  │
  ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │                                                                                 │
  │  1. PROGRESSIVE DISCLOSURE                                                      │
  │     ─────────────────────────                                                   │
  │     • Dashboard shows summary → Click for details                               │
  │     • Lists show key info → Expand for full record                              │
  │     • Actions visible only when applicable                                      │
  │                                                                                 │
  │  2. CONTEXT-AWARE NAVIGATION                                                    │
  │     ──────────────────────────                                                  │
  │     • From Project → Show related WOs, MRs, Costs                               │
  │     • From Invoice → Show related Project, Payments, DO                         │
  │     • Breadcrumbs for deep navigation                                           │
  │                                                                                 │
  │  3. ACTIONABLE ALERTS                                                           │
  │     ─────────────────────                                                       │
  │     • Every alert has a direct action button                                    │
  │     • "Overdue invoice" → [Send Reminder] [Record Payment]                      │
  │     • "Material shortage" → [Create PO] [View Alternatives]                     │
  │                                                                                 │
  │  4. VISUAL STATUS HIERARCHY                                                     │
  │     ─────────────────────────                                                   │
  │     • 🔴 Critical (needs action now)                                            │
  │     • 🟡 Warning (needs attention soon)                                         │
  │     • 🟢 Good (on track)                                                        │
  │     • ⚪ Neutral (pending/draft)                                                │
  │     • 🔵 In Progress (actively working)                                         │
  │                                                                                 │
  │  5. INDONESIAN LOCALIZATION                                                     │
  │     ─────────────────────────                                                   │
  │     • Currency: Rp with thousands separator (.)                                 │
  │     • Date: DD MMM YYYY (27 Des 2024)                                           │
  │     • Tax: PPN 11% clearly shown                                                │
  │     • Terms: Mix of Indonesian business terms where appropriate                 │
  │                                                                                 │
  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  3. MOBILE-FIRST CONSIDERATIONS

  For field workers (installers, site supervisors):

  ┌───────────────────────┐
  │ 📱 MOBILE VIEW        │
  ├───────────────────────┤
  │                       │
  │  WO-2024-156          │
  │  ───────────────────  │
  │                       │
  │  Solar Bekasi         │
  │  Progress: 75%        │
  │                       │
  │  ┌─────────────────┐  │
  │  │  [📸 Add Photo] │  │
  │  └─────────────────┘  │
  │                       │
  │  ┌─────────────────┐  │
  │  │ [✓ Record Work]│  │
  │  └─────────────────┘  │
  │                       │
  │  Today's Tasks:       │
  │  ☑ Cable tray done    │
  │  ☐ AC wiring          │
  │  ☐ Test connections   │
  │                       │
  │  Materials Used:      │
  │  [+ Quick Add]        │
  │                       │
  └───────────────────────┘

  4. KEYBOARD SHORTCUTS (Power Users)

  Global:
    Cmd/Ctrl + K  → Quick search (universal search bar)
    G then D      → Go to Dashboard
    G then Q      → Go to Quotations
    G then P      → Go to Projects
    G then I      → Go to Inventory

  In Lists:
    N             → New record
    E             → Edit selected
    /             → Focus search
    Enter         → Open selected

  In Forms:
    Cmd/Ctrl + S  → Save
    Esc           → Cancel/Close
    Tab           → Next field

  5. COMPONENT LIBRARY RECOMMENDATIONS

  | Component    | Purpose                | Example                   |
  |--------------|------------------------|---------------------------|
  | Status Badge | Show state at a glance | 🟢 COMPLETED              |
  | Progress Bar | Project/WO progress    | ████████░░ 80%            |
  | Stat Card    | KPI display            | Cash Balance with trend   |
  | Data Table   | List views             | Sortable, filterable      |
  | Kanban Board | Pipeline views         | Quotation stages          |
  | Timeline     | Project milestones     | Gantt-lite                |
  | Split View   | List + Detail          | Invoice list with preview |

⏺ ---
  SUMMARY

  I've deeply explored your akuntansi backend (59 models, comprehensive API) and created ASCII wireframes covering the complete user journey for an EPC-focused SPA:

  User Journeys Covered:

  1. Executive Dashboard - Cash, AR/AP, project status at a glance
  2. Sales Journey - Quotation pipeline, quote editor with BOM integration
  3. Project Execution - Project dashboard, work order tracking, cost control
  4. Procurement - MRP planning, PO management, goods receipt
  5. Inventory - Stock overview, material requisition, issue workflow
  6. Finance - AR/AP aging, payment processing, financial reports
  7. Manufacturing - BOM management with cost comparison
  8. Subcontractor - Work order tracking, retention management

  Key UX Principles:

  - Value-first: Each screen emphasizes what matters to that user
  - Action-oriented: Alerts always have direct action buttons
  - Project-centric: Everything connects back to projects (EPC DNA)
  - Mobile-aware: Field workers need simplified mobile views
  - Indonesian context: Rupiah formatting, PPN, local terminology
